---

<Base
  title="Male Tummy Tuck in Houston, TX | The Oaks Plastic Surgery"
  description="Male Tummy Tuck in Houston, TX at The Oaks Plastic Surgery. Board-certified plastic surgeons offering personalized care."
  headerTitle="Male Tummy Tuck in Houston, TX"
  headerImage="/img/male-breast-hero.jpg"
  headerMarginBottom={60}
  canonical="https://theoaksplasticsurgery.com/male-tummy-tuck-houston"
>
<section class="mb-0">
                <div class="container">
                    <div class="row">
                        <div class="col-lg-8 offset-lg-2">
                            <p class="wow fadeInUp lead text-center">
                                A male tummy tuck can help close gaps in your abdominal muscles, remove excess skin and fat, and restore abdominal contours after weight loss. <a href='/danielle-andry-houston'>Dr. Danielle Andry</a> and <a href='/nandi-wijay-houston'>Dr. Nandi Wijay</a> at The Oaks Plastic Surgery (TOPS) in Houston are very experienced in male tummy tucks techniques. 
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>
            <section class="mb-0 pb-240">
                <div class="container-fluid">
                    
                </div>
            </section>            
            <section class="text-section pb-240">
                <div class="container">
                    <div class="row">
                        <h2 class="wow fadeInUp center text-center"> </h2>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div data-jarallax-element="-150" class="text-section-box"></div>
                <div class="container">
                    <div class="row text-row">
                        <div class="col-lg-6">
                            <div class="text-section-block">
                                <h3>After Massive Weight Loss</h3>
                                <p>
                                    For many who have achieved massive weight loss, excess skin is more than a cosmetic issue. If your extra skin is causing issues with hygiene, mobility, back pain, rashes, or infections, you may be eligible to have your male tummy tuck paid for by insurance.
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    If you suffer from these symptoms, the TOPS Houston team will work with your insurance company to see if all or part of your surgery is covered. We find that insurance companies rarely cover male liposuction or body contouring as they are considered cosmetic procedures but sometimes cover the skin removal portion of your male tummy tuck.
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    In some cases, weight loss is significant enough to result in excess skin that cannot be corrected by traditional male abdominoplasty. This typically happens when there is large amounts of skin around the upper abdominals or belly button area. In these cases, you might benefit from specialized tummy tucks like corset abdominoplasty or fleur de lis abdominoplasty. 
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    Whatever your situation, your TOPS Houston plastic surgeon will work with you to determine what kind of male tummy tuck is best for you. 
                                </p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="text-section-block">
                                <h3>Who is a candidate for male tummy tucks at TOPS Houston?</h3>
                                <p>The plastic surgeons at TOPS Houston hear the same concerns from most of their male tummy tuck patients. Many of our patients come to us after significant weight loss, hoping to finally see the results of their hard work. They’re often self-conscious about excess skin after weight loss or stubborn fat around their midsection.</p>
                                <p>A male tummy tuck at TOPS Houston can help you tighten your core, shed unsightly excess skin, and even remove or lessen the appearance of stretch marks. Any male with abdominal separation or excess skin and fat near the abdominals is a potential candidate for a male tummy tuck at TOPS Houston.</p>
                            </div>                            
                        </div>

                        <div class="col-lg-6 pt-lg-5">
                            <div class="text-section-block">
                                <h3>Why choose TOPS Houston for your male tummy tuck?</h3>
                                <p class="align-content-end">
                                <ul>
                                    <li>TOPS Houston doctors are talented plastic surgeons and focus on minimizing scars from your male tummy tuck </li>
                                    <li>Our surgeons trained under one of the foremost innovators in contouring for patients who have achieved massive weight loss.</li>
                                    <li>Small scar revisions and minor contouring that can be performed during your procedure are included free of charge.</li>
                                    <li>For male liposuction candidates, liposuction of the waist and abdomen are included without additional fees from your surgeon. (Note: The increased operative time might result in increased facility fees.)</li>
                                </ul>
                                </p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="text-section-block">
                                <h3>What can you expect at your initial male tummy tuck consultation at TOPS Houston?</h3>
                                <p class="align-content-end">
                                    At your initial consultation for you male tummy tuck, Dr. Andry or Dr. Wijay will:
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>Discuss your vision for your surgery</li>
                                    <li>Perform an exam, including measurements and photographs</li>
                                    <li>Discuss the different male tummy tuck surgical procedures that are right for you</li>
                                    <li>Address all of your questions and concerns</li>
                                    <li>Give you a packet of information on male tummy tucks with instructions for before and after surgery</li>
                                </ul>
                                </p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="text-section-block">
                                <h3>What can you expect on the day of your male tummy tuck at TOPS Houston?</h3>
                                <p class="align-content-end">
                                    In the preoperative room, you’ll have a chance to ask any final questions about your surgery and to meet your anesthesiologist and the rest of your cosmetic surgery team. Male tummy tucks typically take 3-4 hours.
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    Your family will be updated about your progress throughout surgery. After the procedure, your TOPS Houston plastic surgeon will speak with you to review the surgery and post-operative instructions.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
